Jerome Amerika was found guilty of raping and murdering his ex-girlfriend&#8217;s 10-year-old sister. CAPE TOWN - Sentencing proceedings against a 23-year-old man convicted of raping and killing his ex-girlfriend's 10-year-old sister in Paarl will get underway on Monday. Jerome Amerika was convicted in the Western Cape High Court on Thursday.He was arrested after Shamonique Claasen's body was found in a relative's house that stood adjacent to her parent's wendy house in February.Shamonique Claasen was raped and strangled in a room the accused had slept in.Her decomposed body was found wrapped in plastic bags and a blanket, days before her 11th birthday.Groenheuwel resident Willie Petersen knew the victim and says they are eager to put the matter behind them.Judge Robert Henney says Jerome Amerika was a poor witness.Henney found that his version of events was highly improbable and his guilt was beyond reasonable doubt.(Edited by Zamangwane Shange)